{
  "name": "show-in-progress-spinners-on-20260406-0925",
  "idea": "Show in-progress spinners on timeline clips when tasks are actively running for them (image editing, video generation, etc). When a task is created that targets a generation shown on the timeline, a spinner should appear on the corresponding clip immediately. It should update/disappear when the task completes. This should work for any task type - image generation, video generation, image editing. The spinner should show on the clip overlay (like the stale variant badge position pattern). Key questions to research: (1) How does the task system work - where are active tasks tracked? Check useActiveTasks, task polling, realtime subscriptions for task status. (2) How do tasks reference generations/shots - what fields link a task to a specific generation or shot? (3) What existing realtime/polling infrastructure can we hook into? (4) How does the video editor currently know about task completion (e.g. for stale variant detection via useStaleVariants realtime subscriptions)? Key files to check: task creation flow (unified_task_creation.md), task worker lifecycle (task_worker_lifecycle.md), realtime system, useStaleVariants.ts realtime subscriptions, any useActiveTasks or task polling hooks.",
